TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$m = random(2,8,2);
$b = random(1,9,1);
$k = random(3,9,2);
$c = random(1,9,1);


$ans = "($c x + $b)/($m - $k x)";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 15:
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
Let \( \ \displaystyle f(x) = \frac{ $m x - $b}{$k x + $c} \). Find and simplify
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
\( f^{-1}(x) = \) \{ ans_rule(30) \} 
$BR
END_TEXT

ANS( fun_cmp( $ans, vars=>'x' ) );

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
Start with our property of inverse functions \( f \left( f^{-1}(x) \right) = x \), and substitute \( y \) for \( f^{-1}(x) \) to get \( f(y)=x \). Now, using the formula for \( f \) we get \( \displaystyle f(y) = \frac{$m y - $b}{$k y + $c} =x \)
and solving for \( y \) yields
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \displaystyle \frac{$m y - $b}{$k y + $c} =x \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ $m y -$b = x($k y+$c) \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ $m y -$b = $k xy + $c x \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ $m y- $k yx = $c x +$b \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ y($m- $k x) = $c x +$b \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \displaystyle y = \frac{$c x + $b}{$m - $k x} \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
Now replacing \( y \) by \( f^{-1}(x) \), we have our formula,
\( \displaystyle f^{-1}(x) = \frac{$c x + $b}{$m - $k x} \).
$BR
END_SOLUTION

      
